.TH "ORKTREE" "1" "2025" "orktree" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
orktree \- git worktree + fuse\-overlayfs manager
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]orktree\f[R] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\f[B]orktree\f[R] creates isolated, copy\-on\-write workspaces from a
git repository.
Each orktree is a git branch paired with a fuse\-overlayfs overlay so
that only files you actually modify consume extra disk space.
.PP
Creating a new orktree is \f[B]zero\-cost\f[R] by default: the existing
checkout (or another orktree\[cq]s merged view) is used as the overlayfs
lowerdir \[em] no files are duplicated.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]check\f[R]
Check prerequisites; print fix commands for missing ones.
.TP
\f[B]init\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]source\f[R] \f[I]path\f[R]]
Initialize orktree in a directory.
.TP
\f[B]switch\f[R] \f[I]branch\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]from\f[R] \f[I]base\f[R]] [\f[B]\[en]no\-git\f[R]]
Enter an orktree, auto\-creating it if it doesn\[cq]t exist.
Use \f[B]\-\f[R] to return to the source root.
.TP
\f[B]ls\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]quiet\f[R]]
List all orktrees with status and path.
.TP
\f[B]path\f[R] \f[I]branch\f[R]
Print workspace path (auto\-creates if absent).
.TP
\f[B]rm\f[R] \f[I]branch\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]force\f[R]]
Unmount overlay, deregister git worktree, delete state.
.TP
\f[B]shell\-init\f[R] [\f[B]\[en]shell\f[R] \f[I]bash\f[R]|\f[I]zsh\f[R]]
Print shell integration snippet (eval in .bashrc/.zshrc).
.SH SHELL INTEGRATION
Add to your shell startup file:
.IP
.EX
eval \[dq]$(orktree shell\-init)\[dq]
.EE
.PP
This enables \f[B]cd\-on\-switch\f[R] and \f[B]tab completion\f[R].
When shell integration is active, \f[CR]orktree switch <branch>\f[R]
changes your working directory to the orktree workspace.
.SH ZERO\-COST ORKTREES
By default, \f[B]orktree switch\f[R] uses the existing checkout as the
overlayfs lowerdir \[em] no files are copied.
Use \f[B]\[en]from\f[R] to branch from a specific base:
.IP
.EX
# Branch from source root (zero\-cost)
orktree switch fix\-parser

# Stack on top of an existing orktree (zero\-cost)
orktree switch fix\-parser\-v2 \-\-from fix\-parser

# Branch from an older commit (conventional checkout)
orktree switch hotfix \-\-from v1.2.3
.EE
.SH PREREQUISITES
Run \f[B]orktree check\f[R] to verify:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]fuse\-overlayfs\f[R] \[em] rootless copy\-on\-write overlay
filesystem
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]fuse group\f[R] \[em] /dev/fuse access
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]git\f[R] \[em] version control
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[B]<repo>.orktree/\f[R]
Sibling directory created next to the source root.
Contains state.json, the .overlayfs/ internals, and one merged-view directory per branch.
.TP
\f[B]<repo>.orktree/state.json\f[R]
Per\-repository orktree state.
.TP
\f[B]<repo>.orktree/.overlayfs/<id>/\f[R]
Internal fuse\-overlayfs upper, work, and git worktree registration directories.

